01:20:14,110 --> 01:20:15,870
You invited him into
your bed, didn't you?

1257
01:20:15,880 --> 01:20:16,480
Your Honor!

1258
01:20:16,480 --> 01:20:19,450
He attacked me! Strike the question
and answer from the record.

1259
01:20:19,450 --> 01:20:23,450
Mr. Friedman, no more of this.
You understand me?

1260
01:20:23,450 --> 01:20:25,520
Yes, Your Honor.
Yes, of course. I'm sorry.

1261
01:20:27,290 --> 01:20:31,060
Now, your bedroom is just below the room
where the maid slept?

1262
01:20:31,060 --> 01:20:32,590
Yes.

1263
01:20:32,590 --> 01:20:35,100
Did you scream for help?

1264
01:20:35,100 --> 01:20:37,100
I couldn't.
He had a knife.

1265
01:20:37,100 --> 01:20:39,800
Did he hold the knife
as he removed his clothing?

1266
01:20:40,840 --> 01:20:42,500
He must have.

1267
01:20:42,500 --> 01:20:46,870
So he removed his pants, belt,
zipper, whatever, with one hand?

1268
01:20:48,480 --> 01:20:50,010
Apparently so.

1269
01:20:51,080 --> 01:20:52,780
You told Mr. Willis

1270
01:20:52,780 --> 01:20:54,780
that you fought him,
but he overpowered you.

1271
01:20:54,780 --> 01:20:57,120
- Is that right?
- Yes.

1272
01:20:57,120 --> 01:21:00,750
There was a phone
right next to your bed.

1273
01:21:00,760 --> 01:21:04,360
- Did you attempt to use it?
- No. I was terrified.

1274
01:21:04,360 --> 01:21:08,700
Afraid to use the phone or scream for help,
but not afraid to fight back?

1275
01:21:08,700 --> 01:21:11,400
You have no idea what it feels like
to be so afraid.

1276
01:21:12,470 --> 01:21:15,000
But at no point...
at no point

1277
01:21:15,000 --> 01:21:17,770
during the hours and hours
that the two of you were together

1278
01:21:17,770 --> 01:21:21,710
did you ever attempt to make any calls,
to escape, to raise your voice for help?

1279
01:21:21,710 --> 01:21:24,710
- Object. This is argument.
- I was scared for my life!

1280
01:21:24,710 --> 01:21:26,810
Sustained.
The jury will disregard the question.

1281
01:21:26,820 --> 01:21:29,120
You knew you had been unfaithful
to your husband.

1282
01:21:29,120 --> 01:21:31,480
You were terrified of what he would do
to you if he found out.

1283
01:21:31,490 --> 01:21:33,550
And you wanted to get away.
He is badgering the witness!

1284
01:21:33,560 --> 01:21:36,660
That is not true! I was forced
to leave the house. He bound me!

1285
01:21:36,660 --> 01:21:39,290
He gagged me
and he dragged me to the car.

1286
01:21:39,290 --> 01:21:41,630
The police stopped the car?

1287
01:21:41,630 --> 01:21:44,000
Yes.
But still you did not scream?

1288
01:21:44,000 --> 01:21:48,500
- He had a knife!
- Right. Right. The knife.

1289
01:21:48,500 --> 01:21:52,140
As you testified, you were afraid that
he was gonna slash your throat

1290
01:21:52,140 --> 01:21:54,510
from the front seat
of the car, was it?

1291
01:21:54,510 --> 01:21:56,640
I couldn't make a sound.

1292
01:21:56,650 --> 01:21:59,880
- Because of the gag?
- Yes.

1293
01:22:01,080 --> 01:22:03,720
Mrs. Strubing,

1294
01:22:03,720 --> 01:22:06,420
this Exhibit "I" is identical to the gag
that he used?

1295
01:22:06,420 --> 01:22:08,660
Yes.

1296
01:22:08,660 --> 01:22:11,220
Let's just show the jury
what he did then.

1297
01:22:11,230 --> 01:22:16,900
Mrs. Strubing, please, please instruct
Mr. Marshall, if you would.

1298
01:22:20,070 --> 01:22:23,170
The gag was between your lips.
Is that correct, Mrs. Strubing?

1299
01:22:23,170 --> 01:22:25,310
Yes. That's correct.

1300
01:22:33,750 --> 01:22:37,180
Is this about right?

1301
01:22:37,190 --> 01:22:40,590
No, it was a bit tighter than that.

1302
01:22:43,960 --> 01:22:45,960
How 'bout this, ma'am?

1303
01:22:45,960 --> 01:22:47,490
Yes, that's about it.

1304
01:23:00,440 --> 01:23:03,840
Now, you could have
done that, Mrs. Strubing.

1305
01:23:05,080 --> 01:23:06,810
He would have killed me.

1306
01:23:06,820 --> 01:23:10,420
- Who would have killed you? Your husband?
- Objection!

1307
01:23:10,420 --> 01:23:12,590
- Quiet, Mr. Marshall.
- How dare you speak to me that way.

1308
01:23:12,590 --> 01:23:14,530
There was a policeman
standing not three feet

1309
01:23:14,540 --> 01:23:16,490
away from you. You did
not call out for help.

1310
01:23:16,490 --> 01:23:18,170
Instead, Joseph drove
on to the reservoir.

1311
01:23:18,190 --> 01:23:19,390
I'm warning you. No speaking!

1312
01:23:19,390 --> 01:23:22,260
You bolted from the car because
you were ashamed of what you had done

1313
01:23:22,260 --> 01:23:24,460
- with another man, with a colored man!
- Objection!

1314
01:23:24,470 --> 01:23:28,070
One more word out of you and
I will hold you in contempt!

1315
01:23:28,070 --> 01:23:31,070
You were afraid of what your husband
would do to you if he found out.

1316
01:23:31,070 --> 01:23:33,240
Afraid that you were pregnant
with a colored child.

1317
01:23:33,240 --> 01:23:35,340
- Objection! This is argument!
- Sustained.

1318
01:23:35,340 --> 01:23:38,310
- Jury will disregard.
- You jumped into that water.

1319
01:23:38,310 --> 01:23:40,850
- You wanted to end it all.
- Jumped? I was thrown.

1320
01:23:40,850 --> 01:23:44,950
I was thrown. My hands were tied.
He tried to kill me!

1321
01:23:44,950 --> 01:23:49,760
Your hands were not tied,
Mrs. Strubing.

1322
01:23:49,760 --> 01:23:52,330
You were able
to remove your coat

1323
01:23:52,330 --> 01:23:55,160
and let it float in the water
as you swam to shore.

1324
01:23:55,160 --> 01:23:59,130
That's not true. That's a lie.
He gagged me. He tied me.

1325
01:23:59,130 --> 01:24:00,400
Raped me.

1326
01:24:04,540 --> 01:24:10,080
I am so... so sorry for your unhappiness,
Mrs. Strubing.

1327
01:24:12,610 --> 01:24:14,010
No more questions.

1328
01:24:15,220 --> 01:24:18,750
- Mr. Willis?
- I have no questions.

1329
01:24:27,830 --> 01:24:30,560
How can we put Spell on the stand
with all this baggage?

1330
01:24:30,570 --> 01:24:32,730
The jury needs
to hear him deny it.

1331
01:24:32,730 --> 01:24:35,170
And you bring out
all the bad stuff yourself.

1332
01:24:35,170 --> 01:24:37,540
Don't leave anything for Willis.

1333
01:24:37,540 --> 01:24:39,840
What happens to the organization
if we lose?

1334
01:24:39,840 --> 01:24:41,980
I don't even want
to think about it.

1335
01:24:43,880 --> 01:24:46,380
You could blame me.

1336
01:24:46,380 --> 01:24:48,420
You're one of us now, Sam.

1337
01:24:48,420 --> 01:24:50,820
Haven't you noticed?

1338
01:24:50,820 --> 01:24:55,320
In the papers they write, "Sam Friedman
and Thurgood Marshall of the NAACP."

1339
01:25:01,360 --> 01:25:04,300
Joseph, please tell the jury
where you were raised.

1340
01:25:05,370 --> 01:25:06,800
Louisiana.

1341
01:25:08,700 --> 01:25:12,610
- You have a wife and two children, right?
- Uh-huh.

1342
01:25:12,610 --> 01:25:16,680
Even though you have a wife, you have
another woman in White Plains, is it?

1343
01:25:16,680 --> 01:25:18,380
Yes.
What's he doing?

1344
01:25:18,380 --> 01:25:20,710
- Ever served in the army, Joseph?
- Yes, sir.

1345
01:25:20,720 --> 01:25:23,780
Fort Benning, Georgia,
six years. Discharged.

1346
01:25:23,790 --> 01:25:26,450
That was
a dishonorable discharge?

1347
01:25:26,460 --> 01:25:28,350
Yes.

1348
01:25:28,360 --> 01:25:31,220
Then you moved north?
That's right.

1349
01:25:31,230 --> 01:25:34,730
Before working for the Strubings,
you worked for another family in Greenwich?

1350
01:25:34,730 --> 01:25:35,930
Yes, sir.

1351
01:25:35,930 --> 01:25:38,060
They accused you of stealing
and fired you.

1352
01:25:38,070 --> 01:25:39,900
Yes, sir.

1353
01:25:39,900 --> 01:25:41,630
And when you worked
for the Strubings,

1354
01:25:41,640 --> 01:25:43,940
did you run into
any other difficulties?

1355
01:25:43,940 --> 01:25:47,770
- No, sir.
- Did the Strubings treat you well, Joseph?

1356
01:25:47,780 --> 01:25:50,140
She was always real nice to me.

1357
01:25:50,150 --> 01:25:52,450
What about Mr. Strubing?

1358
01:25:58,120 --> 01:25:59,520
Was he mean to you?

1359
01:26:00,550 --> 01:26:02,590
He was mean to everybody.

1360
01:26:02,590 --> 01:26:05,020
It is what you did.
Don't lie to me.

1361
01:26:07,560 --> 01:26:10,230
- Watch where you're standing.
- Yes, sir.

1362
01:26:19,410 --> 01:26:21,370
Just a second, Joseph.
I'm sorry.

1363
01:26:23,010 --> 01:26:24,880
That's quite all right, ma'am.

1364
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:32,290
On the night of this incident,

1365
01:26:32,290 --> 01:26:34,820
why did you go into
Mrs. Strubing's room?

1366
01:26:34,820 --> 01:26:38,760
To ask her for money. I had to pay
a man I'd been playing cards with.

1367
01:26:40,030 --> 01:26:41,690
What happened
when you got to the room?

1368
01:26:50,500 --> 01:26:52,740
I knocked on the door.

1369
01:26:53,840 --> 01:26:55,680
Come in.

1370
01:26:55,680 --> 01:26:58,850
I could tell she'd been sad.
She was crying.

1371
01:26:58,850 --> 01:27:01,610
- Are you okay, ma'am?
- What do you want, Joseph?

1372
01:27:02,950 --> 01:27:05,020
It can wait, Mrs. Strubing.

1373
01:27:05,020 --> 01:27:07,190
But she told me to stay,
ask my question.

1374
01:27:07,190 --> 01:27:09,790
I told her I needed some money.
She asked what for.

1375
01:27:11,030 --> 01:27:12,760
There's a man I owe.

1376
01:27:13,860 --> 01:27:15,600
Ah.

1377
01:27:23,340 --> 01:27:25,640
So she went to the bureau.

1378
01:27:28,580 --> 01:27:31,740
She said, "Is this enough for you, Joseph?"
I said, "Yes, ma'am. Thank you."

1379
01:27:31,750 --> 01:27:33,910
But she didn't give it to me.
Then she asked me...

1380
01:27:33,920 --> 01:27:37,980
I'm not awful like him,
am I, Joseph?

1381
01:27:37,990 --> 01:27:39,990
No, ma'am.

1382
01:27:49,160 --> 01:27:51,360
Joseph.

1383
01:27:51,370 --> 01:27:53,970
She asked me not to
leave her alone that night.

1384
01:27:54,900 --> 01:27:58,140
And, uh... I didn't.

1385
01:28:21,400 --> 01:28:23,400
Then what happened?

1386
01:28:23,400 --> 01:28:25,800
Well, we went down to the living room,
me and her.

1387
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:28,940
- We had a drink together.
- What did the two of you talk about?

1388
01:28:30,570 --> 01:28:32,340
She told me he beats her.

1389
01:28:33,140 --> 01:28:34,610
Who beats her?

1390
01:28:41,880 --> 01:28:43,820
Who did that?

1391
01:28:46,890 --> 01:28:48,350
My husband.

1392
01:29:13,650 --> 01:29:16,080
Did she ever resist you, Joseph?

1393
01:29:16,080 --> 01:29:19,050
No, she didn't.
Not at all.

1394
01:29:21,590 --> 01:29:23,620
What happened next?

1395
01:29:23,630 --> 01:29:27,060
We were lying on the sofa.

1396
01:29:39,370 --> 01:29:42,010
Oh, God.

1397
01:29:42,010 --> 01:29:45,380
- And she heard some dogs barking.
- Joseph.

1398
01:29:45,380 --> 01:29:48,680
She was convinced somebody was gonna
come to the house and find us together.

1399
01:29:48,680 --> 01:29:51,250
Get up. Get up!

1400
01:29:52,450 --> 01:29:54,620
Nobody gonna wake up.

1401
01:29:54,620 --> 01:29:58,020
She started panicking. I told her
there's no one coming. Everything's fine.

1402
01:29:58,030 --> 01:30:00,830
But she was insisting on,
"We gotta get out of here.

1403
01:30:00,830 --> 01:30:04,330
We gotta get out of here right now."
So we left the house.

1404
01:30:04,330 --> 01:30:08,300
We go down to the car,
and we drive around for a bit.

1405
01:30:08,300 --> 01:30:11,970
She sat in the back,
so it don't look wrong.

1406
01:30:11,970 --> 01:30:14,940
Then the cop car
come up from behind.

1407
01:30:16,410 --> 01:30:18,180
She get real scared.

1408
01:30:18,180 --> 01:30:20,180
She say...
Why don't you lie down and keep quiet?

1409
01:30:20,180 --> 01:30:21,810
I can't be seen
with a colored man.

1410
01:30:21,820 --> 01:30:24,250
I say, "You lie down
and keep quiet then."

1411
01:30:24,250 --> 01:30:26,490
Don't move. Shh. Shh.

1412
01:30:27,690 --> 01:30:29,320
Oh.
Shh, shh.

1413
01:30:33,890 --> 01:30:36,360
Where'd you get this car, boy?

1414
01:30:36,360 --> 01:30:39,800
I'm a chauffeur, sir. Belongs to John
Strubing. Greenwich, Connecticut.

1415
01:30:42,100 --> 01:30:43,970
Identification.
Yes, sir.

1416
01:30:53,180 --> 01:30:55,010
Drive slower, boy.
Yes, sir.

1417
01:30:55,020 --> 01:30:56,950
Get your ass
out of Port Chester.

1418
01:30:56,950 --> 01:30:58,520
On my way right now, sir.
Thank you.

1419
01:30:58,520 --> 01:31:00,220
What happened next?

1420
01:31:00,220 --> 01:31:04,160
We get to the reservoir,
and, uh, she scream at me.

1421
01:31:05,290 --> 01:31:06,890
Joseph, stop the car.
Stop the car!

1422
01:31:06,900 --> 01:31:09,060
Joseph, stop the car!

1423
01:31:09,060 --> 01:31:11,130
What's the matter?

1424
01:31:11,130 --> 01:31:13,530
She keeps shaking her head
and saying, "What have I done?"

1425
01:31:13,540 --> 01:31:15,740
Everything's gonna be fine,
Mrs. Strubing.

1426
01:31:15,740 --> 01:31:18,040
Just take a deep breath,
okay? No, no, no, no.

1427
01:31:18,040 --> 01:31:21,070
No, you don't understand.

1428
01:31:21,080 --> 01:31:24,480
Maybe we should just
go back to the house, huh?

1429
01:31:24,480 --> 01:31:27,780
You don't understand.
You don't understand.

1430
01:31:27,780 --> 01:31:31,780
She keeps saying, "I'm gonna get pregnant."
"No, you ain't," I said.

1431
01:31:31,790 --> 01:31:34,420
- You're not gonna get pregnant.
- I can't have a colored child.

1432
01:31:34,420 --> 01:31:36,820
You're not gonna have
no babies at all, okay?

1433
01:31:36,830 --> 01:31:39,790
I say,
"Just let me take you home."

1434
01:31:40,760 --> 01:31:42,090
And she screamed at me.

1435
01:31:42,100 --> 01:31:43,930
Let me out of the car!

1436
01:31:43,930 --> 01:31:45,670
I'm gonna tell everybody
you raped me!

1437
01:31:46,930 --> 01:31:48,600
She go to open the door,
and I grabbed her.

1438
01:31:48,600 --> 01:31:50,740
Let me go!
Just to keep her there.

1439
01:31:50,740 --> 01:31:53,940
That's when she scratches my arm.
Mrs. Strubing.

1440
01:31:53,940 --> 01:31:55,740
Hey. Hey!

1441
01:31:57,080 --> 01:31:59,280
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1442
01:31:59,280 --> 01:32:02,250
Mrs. Strubing,
what you doing up there?

1443
01:32:02,250 --> 01:32:04,280
I yell at her
to come back, but...

1444
01:32:04,290 --> 01:32:07,090
Come on down right now.
Let's get in the car and go home.

1445
01:32:07,090 --> 01:32:08,790
She just turned away.

1446
01:32:08,790 --> 01:32:10,560
Mrs. Strub...

1447
01:32:25,840 --> 01:32:30,410
Joseph, did you rape
Mrs. Strubing?

1448
01:32:32,280 --> 01:32:35,850
No. I did not.

1449
01:32:37,020 --> 01:32:38,950
Thank you, Joseph.

1450
01:32:41,820 --> 01:32:43,260
Your witness.

1451
01:32:46,630 --> 01:32:48,460
Not bad.

1452
01:32:48,460 --> 01:32:51,130
You wouldn't lie to the jury, would
you, Joseph? Not bad at all.

1453
01:32:51,130 --> 01:32:52,800
No, sir, I wouldn't.

1454
01:32:52,800 --> 01:32:54,700
But the fact is,
you are a liar, aren't you?

1455
01:32:54,700 --> 01:32:56,640
Objection!
Argumentative.

1456
01:32:56,640 --> 01:33:00,140
Overruled.
It's cross-examination.

1457
01:33:01,740 --> 01:33:03,180
He's okay.

1458
01:33:03,180 --> 01:33:06,210
When you married
your first wife, Hattie,

1459
01:33:06,210 --> 01:33:09,520
you swore to God you'd be faithful to her,
did you not?

1460
01:33:09,520 --> 01:33:13,450
- Yes, sir.
- But you weren't. It was a lie.

1461
01:33:14,860 --> 01:33:16,660
You could say.

1462
01:33:16,660 --> 01:33:19,330
You told her you'd take care
of your children, didn't you?

1463
01:33:19,330 --> 01:33:22,130
Yes, sir.
But you haven't, have you?

1464
01:33:23,430 --> 01:33:25,830
Not so much as I should.

1465
01:33:25,830 --> 01:33:29,670
Then you were in the service
and you swore to honor your country.

1466
01:33:29,670 --> 01:33:31,700
But that was a lie too.
No.

1467
01:33:31,710 --> 01:33:36,340
Then you came north and you stole from
your first employer?

1468
01:33:36,340 --> 01:33:38,140
When the police picked
you up, you lied to

1469
01:33:38,150 --> 01:33:40,080
them about your whereabouts
the night before.

1470
01:33:40,080 --> 01:33:42,750
- Didn't you?
- Yes, I did.

1471
01:33:42,750 --> 01:33:46,420
You gave a statement under oath
that you were in a bar all night.

1472
01:33:46,420 --> 01:33:48,420
Yes.

1473
01:33:48,420 --> 01:33:51,260
So you lied to your wife,
you lied to the State of Louisiana,

1474
01:33:51,260 --> 01:33:53,790
you lied to the police,
you lied to God.

1475
01:33:53,800 --> 01:33:56,060
Why should anyone
believe you now?

1476
01:33:56,060 --> 01:33:59,770
I don't know why they should,
except it's the truth.

1477
01:33:59,770 --> 01:34:05,470
The truth? If it's the truth,
why not tell it from the beginning?

1478
01:34:05,470 --> 01:34:08,710
If you're an innocent man,
why lie?

1479
01:34:10,940 --> 01:34:13,710
Why lie, Mr. Spell? Answer the question.
Tell him, Joseph.

1480
01:34:13,720 --> 01:34:18,450
If you were an innocent man,
why would you lie?

1481
01:34:18,450 --> 01:34:21,920
I tell the police I was with her,
it was what she wanted?

1482
01:34:21,920 --> 01:34:24,060
If it's the truth.

1483
01:34:24,060 --> 01:34:28,230
In Louisiana, you know what they do to me
for being with a white woman like that?

1484
01:34:28,230 --> 01:34:31,100
If they don't kill me
right then and there,

1485
01:34:31,100 --> 01:34:35,170
soon enough the others come,
they drag me off, they tie me up,

1486
01:34:35,170 --> 01:34:37,200
they cut off my manhood.

1487
01:34:39,510 --> 01:34:42,240
And then I'd be swingin'
off the branch of some tree.

1488
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:46,310
So... why'd I lie,
Mr. Willis?

1489
01:34:47,680 --> 01:34:50,080
Because the truth
gets me killed.

1490
01:34:50,080 --> 01:34:52,050
That's why.

1491
01:34:53,020 --> 01:34:54,550
I move the answer be stricken.

1492
01:35:10,340 --> 01:35:12,240
The answer will stand.

1493
01:35:19,810 --> 01:35:21,410
Mr. Willis?

1494
01:35:24,650 --> 01:35:26,690
Nothing further, Your Honor.

1495
01:35:41,070 --> 01:35:43,040
You know what?

1496
01:35:43,040 --> 01:35:45,810
It finally looks like a respectable
law office in here.

1497
01:35:48,640 --> 01:35:50,310
Come in.

1498
01:35:52,080 --> 01:35:54,480
There's someone here
to see you, Mr. Marshall.

1499
01:35:57,020 --> 01:35:58,450
Walter?

1500
01:36:00,650 --> 01:36:03,060
What are you doing here?
Can we talk?

1501
01:36:04,390 --> 01:36:07,730
I'll just move
to Irwin's office.

1502
01:36:11,600 --> 01:36:13,430
Come on, Walter.

1503
01:36:13,430 --> 01:36:15,270
What is this?

1504
01:36:15,270 --> 01:36:18,200
Fourteen-year-old boy in Mississippi.
They say he killed a cop.

1505
01:36:18,210 --> 01:36:21,040
He needs a lawyer.

1506
01:36:21,040 --> 01:36:24,040
- And I have to leave tonight?
- Uh-huh.

1507
01:36:24,050 --> 01:36:26,210
He ready with the summation?

1508
01:36:26,210 --> 01:36:29,050
Sam? He will be.

1509
01:36:29,050 --> 01:36:32,320
Then there's no reason for you to stay.
I'll take care of everything.

1510
01:36:47,200 --> 01:36:48,770
You get the picture
Renie left you?

1511
01:36:49,370 --> 01:36:51,270
Ah, yes.

1512
01:36:51,270 --> 01:36:55,010
Now, what kind of plane is this?

1513
01:36:56,110 --> 01:37:00,050
She said
it's supposed to be you.

1514
01:37:00,050 --> 01:37:02,310
Those are ears, not wings.
Ah!

1515
01:37:03,780 --> 01:37:05,680
She's quite a talent.

1516
01:37:07,820 --> 01:37:09,590
You were right, you know.

1517
01:37:09,590 --> 01:37:12,960
About what?
"Why would she lie?"

1518
01:37:12,960 --> 01:37:14,630
Mmm.

1519
01:37:14,630 --> 01:37:16,700
That is the question
we needed to answer.

1520
01:37:17,900 --> 01:37:19,370
Well...

1521
01:37:21,170 --> 01:37:26,540
I'm thankful Renie got to see there's men
like you in the world.

1522
01:37:30,340 --> 01:37:33,310
I don't understand how you can leave
before closing arguments.

1523
01:37:33,310 --> 01:37:37,180
Doesn't do anyone any good having me
sit around waiting on a verdict.

1524
01:37:37,190 --> 01:37:39,290
What if something comes up?

1525
01:37:39,290 --> 01:37:41,950
The case is in, Sam.

1526
01:37:41,960 --> 01:37:44,960
Walter will represent the NAACP.

1527
01:37:44,960 --> 01:37:46,430
And you'll be there for Spell.

1528
01:37:53,770 --> 01:37:56,800
Sam, did you know
I only have one testicle?

1529
01:37:56,800 --> 01:37:59,840
Um... no.

1530
01:37:59,840 --> 01:38:01,770
Yeah.

1531
01:38:01,780 --> 01:38:06,150
In my college years, I found myself running
from a gang of bigots

1532
01:38:06,150 --> 01:38:09,680
in a part of town they didn't believe
I should be in.

1533
01:38:09,680 --> 01:38:11,880
My buddies, they're ahead of me
in a truck.

1534
01:38:11,890 --> 01:38:14,190
I jump for the back,
and I'm pulling myself up,

1535
01:38:14,190 --> 01:38:18,520
but there's a jagged spike
of metal I don't see.

1536
01:38:18,530 --> 01:38:21,630
It slashes
right through my sack.

1537
01:38:21,630 --> 01:38:23,130
Yeah.

1538
01:38:24,500 --> 01:38:26,800
Why am I telling you this?

1539
01:38:26,800 --> 01:38:29,970
Well, I want you to know

1540
01:38:29,970 --> 01:38:32,140
that even sitting
in the back of that pickup,

1541
01:38:32,140 --> 01:38:33,970
my scrotum torn,

1542
01:38:33,980 --> 01:38:37,010
every bump sending shocks
of pain down my leg,

1543
01:38:37,010 --> 01:38:40,080
even that wasn't as excruciating
as sitting there

1544
01:38:40,080 --> 01:38:43,180
watching you argue this case
these past few weeks.

1545
01:38:49,690 --> 01:38:52,160
- But I did learn something.
- Huh?

1546
01:38:53,690 --> 01:38:57,500
I need an army of lawyers
just like you, Sam.

1547
01:38:57,500 --> 01:39:01,070
Lawyers who don't even know
they want to make a difference,

1548
01:39:01,070 --> 01:39:04,770
who with just a little bit of training
can be just as capable as me.

1549
01:39:08,040 --> 01:39:10,980
Well, almost as capable.

1550
01:39:13,710 --> 01:39:16,050
And until then what?

1551
01:39:16,050 --> 01:39:20,120
You just travel around the country
on this crusade?

1552
01:39:20,120 --> 01:39:23,390
Putting out fires
in Mississippi,

1553
01:39:23,390 --> 01:39:26,960
Oklahoma, Bridgeport?

1554
01:39:26,960 --> 01:39:30,200
It's not really fires
I'm after, Sam.

1555
01:39:31,930 --> 01:39:33,700
It's fire itself.

1556
01:39:36,970 --> 01:39:38,670
Get out your pen now.

1557
01:39:40,740 --> 01:39:43,780
Here's the closing argument
you're gonna give.

1558
01:39:43,780 --> 01:39:46,080
Who is telling the truth?

1559
01:39:46,080 --> 01:39:50,880
A woman from a fine family
with an unblemished background,

1560
01:39:50,890 --> 01:39:53,220
or a depraved man,

1561
01:39:53,220 --> 01:39:55,620
a repeat criminal
with no morals,

1562
01:39:55,620 --> 01:39:59,960
a man whose whole life has been composed
of a series of lies?

1563
01:40:01,590 --> 01:40:05,100
Did this decent, church-going,
intelligent woman,

1564
01:40:05,100 --> 01:40:06,930
the graduate of a top college,

1565
01:40:06,930 --> 01:40:10,970
engage in voluntary sexual relations
with her Negro servant

1566
01:40:10,970 --> 01:40:13,270
and then jump
into the water, for what?

1567
01:40:13,270 --> 01:40:16,680
For pleasure,
as the defense would have you believe?

1568
01:40:16,680 --> 01:40:19,080
Of course not.

1569
01:40:19,080 --> 01:40:22,750
Joseph Spell raped
Eleanor Strubing.

1570
01:40:22,750 --> 01:40:26,320
Then he hurled her over the bridge to kill
the only witness to his crime.

1571
01:40:26,320 --> 01:40:30,690
Acquit him, and you will set
a wild panther loose in our midst

1572
01:40:30,690 --> 01:40:32,660
to stalk more victims,

1573
01:40:32,660 --> 01:40:34,860
to threaten the safety
and security

1574
01:40:34,860 --> 01:40:37,660
of each and every woman
in the State of Connecticut.

1575
01:40:37,670 --> 01:40:41,100
As a jury, you have been exposed

1576
01:40:41,100 --> 01:40:44,340
to the darkness
of a sinister man's soul.

1577
01:40:47,110 --> 01:40:50,480
But you're also in a position
of great privilege.

1578
01:40:50,480 --> 01:40:53,050
Because you...

1579
01:40:53,050 --> 01:40:55,680
you have the power

1580
01:40:55,680 --> 01:40:59,250
to do justice
on behalf of all of us.

1581
01:41:00,690 --> 01:41:02,590
Bullshit.
Thank you.

1582
01:41:03,490 --> 01:41:05,420
And God bless.

1583
01:41:13,170 --> 01:41:14,770
Mr. Friedman.

1584
01:41:17,570 --> 01:41:21,870
Why would a woman
like Eleanor Strubing

1585
01:41:21,880 --> 01:41:26,750
consent... no, encourage...
sexual relations

1586
01:41:26,750 --> 01:41:29,050
with a man like Joseph Spell?

1587
01:41:29,050 --> 01:41:31,380
Let me tell you why.

1588
01:41:31,390 --> 01:41:36,420
Eleanor Strubing's story
is nothing less than tragic.

1589
01:41:36,420 --> 01:41:39,360
She is a respectable woman
from a fine family.

1590
01:41:39,360 --> 01:41:41,060
She attended the best schools.

1591
01:41:41,060 --> 01:41:44,660
She went to church
each and every Sunday.

1592
01:41:44,670 --> 01:41:48,270
As the good book says, she was "spotless
as the lamb of God."

1593
01:41:48,270 --> 01:41:52,100
She was "spotless
as the lamb of God."

1594
01:41:52,110 --> 01:41:54,870
She and her husband John
move to Greenwich.

1595
01:41:54,880 --> 01:41:56,940
Oh, he travels frequently,

1596
01:41:56,940 --> 01:42:00,080
leaving her alone in a new town,

1597
01:42:00,080 --> 01:42:01,950
away from her friends
and family,

1598
01:42:02,780 --> 01:42:04,950
in a vast, empty house.

1599
01:42:04,950 --> 01:42:08,220
The pangs of loneliness
hit hard.

1600
01:42:08,220 --> 01:42:10,660
She has some drinks.

1601
01:42:11,590 --> 01:42:12,990
A knock at the door.

1602
01:42:14,590 --> 01:42:16,860
- Joseph.
- Joseph.

1603
01:42:16,860 --> 01:42:20,200
She was not expecting this.

1604
01:42:20,200 --> 01:42:23,070
A young man, a handsome man.

1605
01:42:23,070 --> 01:42:26,610
In a moment of weakness,
her judgment impaired

1606
01:42:26,610 --> 01:42:28,270
by the alcohol
of the evening...

1607
01:42:28,280 --> 01:42:30,640
Consumed by loneliness,

1608
01:42:30,640 --> 01:42:34,380
she invites him to share her bed
to ease her pain.

1609
01:42:34,380 --> 01:42:37,620
As the evening goes on,
she becomes panicked

1610
01:42:37,620 --> 01:42:39,490
that they will be discovered.

1611
01:42:39,490 --> 01:42:43,120
She must leave the house,
must escape her sin.

1612
01:42:44,560 --> 01:42:47,060
- What if she is pregnant...
- And with a colored child?

1613
01:42:47,060 --> 01:42:50,630
What if her husband were to find out?
What would he do to her?

1614
01:42:50,630 --> 01:42:54,430
She cannot live
with the fear, the shame.

1615
01:42:54,440 --> 01:42:57,940
So then there they are,
at the reservoir.

1616
01:42:57,940 --> 01:43:02,740
An opportunity to escape
her life, her despair.

1617
01:43:02,740 --> 01:43:06,280
Joseph tries to hold her back,
but she wrangles free, runs from the car.

1618
01:43:06,280 --> 01:43:10,280
And she plummets into the water.

1619
01:43:10,280 --> 01:43:13,750
Only as soon
as she hits the surface,

1620
01:43:13,750 --> 01:43:16,190
her years of training take over.

1621
01:43:16,190 --> 01:43:18,660
See, she is a swimmer.

1622
01:43:18,660 --> 01:43:21,630
And she simply cannot drown.

1623
01:43:21,630 --> 01:43:24,130
With the zeal
to end her life gone,

1624
01:43:24,130 --> 01:43:26,300
her only escape...

1625
01:43:26,300 --> 01:43:27,870
She must accuse him.

1626
01:43:27,870 --> 01:43:30,440
And so a story is created.

1627
01:43:30,440 --> 01:43:31,770
A web of...

1628
01:43:34,040 --> 01:43:36,310
desperate lies

1629
01:43:36,310 --> 01:43:41,850
filled with inconsistencies,
absurdities,

1630
01:43:42,680 --> 01:43:44,480
reasonable doubts.

1631
01:43:44,490 --> 01:43:48,020
The State must prove its case
beyond a reasonable doubt.

1632
01:43:48,020 --> 01:43:50,390
It must be a clear case.

1633
01:43:50,390 --> 01:43:54,260
No scream for help
all night long.

1634
01:43:55,400 --> 01:43:57,000
Doubt.

1635
01:43:57,000 --> 01:44:00,130
No call on
the four family phones.

1636
01:44:00,130 --> 01:44:02,230
Doubt.

1637
01:44:02,240 --> 01:44:05,140
No cry to the officer
just a few feet away.

1638
01:44:05,140 --> 01:44:06,510
Doubt.

1639
01:44:06,510 --> 01:44:09,340
No rocks on a bridge.

1640
01:44:09,340 --> 01:44:10,540
Doubt.

1641
01:44:10,540 --> 01:44:13,550
Doubt, doubt, doubt.

1642
01:44:15,250 --> 01:44:17,850
The doubt, my friends,

1643
01:44:17,850 --> 01:44:19,590
is overwhelming.

1644
01:44:19,590 --> 01:44:24,660
This is why you must find
Joseph Spell not guilty.

1645
01:44:24,660 --> 01:44:27,090
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

1646
01:44:27,090 --> 01:44:29,560
you've heard the arguments
of counsel.

1647
01:44:29,560 --> 01:44:33,300
You may now retire to the jury room
to begin your deliberations.

1648
01:44:34,370 --> 01:44:35,800
Court is in recess.

1649
01:44:47,180 --> 01:44:49,380
Who is it?

1650
01:44:49,380 --> 01:44:50,920
It's me.

1651
01:44:56,720 --> 01:44:58,190
Mmm!

1652
01:45:01,360 --> 01:45:03,400
You're supposed
to be on a train.

1653
01:45:03,400 --> 01:45:05,500
I have a little time.

1654
01:45:12,540 --> 01:45:14,870
I heard you were looking for me.

1655
01:45:16,410 --> 01:45:19,210
Well, Friedman, it seems you have
beginner's luck.

1656
01:45:19,210 --> 01:45:21,650
John Strubing just called me.

1657
01:45:21,650 --> 01:45:24,720
This whole thing has been a terrible
strain on Ellie, as you can imagine.

1658
01:45:24,720 --> 01:45:27,220
They want it over, now.

1659
01:45:27,220 --> 01:45:29,790
I'm prepared to offer
one final deal.

1660
01:45:29,790 --> 01:45:32,320
What is it?
Five years.

1661
01:45:32,330 --> 01:45:35,960
He'll have to enter a guilty plea right
away and admit he lied on the stand.

1662
01:45:38,000 --> 01:45:40,400
I'll speak with him.
Do it now.

1663
01:45:40,400 --> 01:45:42,870
If the jury comes back in,
the deal is off.

1664
01:45:47,810 --> 01:45:51,480
You'd be out after three years,
with good behavior.

1665
01:45:51,480 --> 01:45:55,350
Possibly sooner.
You think I should take it?

1666
01:45:55,350 --> 01:45:57,350
I don't know
what the jury will do.

1667
01:45:57,350 --> 01:46:00,250
It's a good deal.

1668
01:46:00,250 --> 01:46:02,790
And if they convict me?

1669
01:46:02,790 --> 01:46:05,660
Most likely you'll spend the rest
of your life in a prison cell.

1670
01:46:07,930 --> 01:46:10,060
And I got to decide right away?

1671
01:46:12,330 --> 01:46:14,230
What I gotta do for the deal?

1672
01:46:17,140 --> 01:46:20,440
Admit that you raped her and that you lied
on the witness stand.

1673
01:46:22,040 --> 01:46:24,310
Can I talk
to Mr. Marshall?

1674
01:46:24,310 --> 01:46:27,510
He's on a train probably somewhere
in Tennessee by now.

1675
01:46:27,510 --> 01:46:29,750
I would never be able
to reach him in time.

1676
01:46:31,520 --> 01:46:33,420
What do you think he would say?

1677
01:46:43,030 --> 01:46:44,560
Ah.

1678
01:46:49,540 --> 01:46:51,370
So, give me good news.

1679
01:46:52,470 --> 01:46:54,270
No deal.

1680
01:46:55,980 --> 01:46:58,080
You did advise him
to accept, hmm?

1681
01:46:58,080 --> 01:47:00,710
I told him it was a good offer.

1682
01:47:00,710 --> 01:47:02,650
I told him
what the alternative is.

1683
01:47:02,650 --> 01:47:05,820
I told him if it was me,
I would take it.

1684
01:47:08,020 --> 01:47:12,290
And I told him that no man should ever
confess to a crime he did not commit.

1685
01:47:16,160 --> 01:47:19,260
I thought Jews were supposed
to be smart.

1686
01:47:19,270 --> 01:47:21,270
But you sound
just like the Negro.

1687
01:47:24,100 --> 01:47:26,740
Why, thank you, Lorin.

1688
01:47:26,740 --> 01:47:29,640
That's possibly the greatest compliment
you could've given me.

1689
01:47:56,400 --> 01:47:58,170
There's a verdict.

1690
01:48:09,050 --> 01:48:10,480
Will the foreman
please rise.

1691
01:48:10,480 --> 01:48:13,190
I'm the forewoman, Your Honor.

1692
01:48:14,920 --> 01:48:16,660
Very well.

1693
01:48:16,660 --> 01:48:18,490
Have you reached a verdict?

1694
01:48:18,490 --> 01:48:20,060
We have, Your Honor.

1695
01:48:21,230 --> 01:48:23,500
Mr. Spell.

1696
01:48:23,500 --> 01:48:26,330
Rise and face the jury.
It's time.

1697
01:48:31,400 --> 01:48:33,370
Madame Forewoman,
what is your verdict?

1698
01:48:35,410 --> 01:48:38,340
We, the jury, find,
on the charge of rape,

1699
01:48:38,350 --> 01:48:40,450
that the defendant,
Joseph Spell,

1700
01:48:40,450 --> 01:48:42,150
is not guilty.

1701
01:48:55,030 --> 01:48:56,560
Order.

1702
01:48:59,770 --> 01:49:01,700
Is this your verdict,
so say you all?

1703
01:49:01,700 --> 01:49:03,800
We do, Your Honor.

1704
01:49:03,800 --> 01:49:05,300
That's it, Joseph.

1705
01:49:05,310 --> 01:49:06,940
We did it.

1706
01:49:06,940 --> 01:49:10,380
Mr. Spell, the jury
has found you not guilty.

1707
01:49:10,380 --> 01:49:11,740
You are released from custody.

1708
01:49:12,980 --> 01:49:15,780
Jury is dismissed.
Court is adjourned.

1709
01:49:15,780 --> 01:49:18,180
All rise.

1710
01:49:37,170 --> 01:49:39,470
- Congratulations, Mr. White.
- Thank you.

1711
01:49:43,840 --> 01:49:46,550
Mr. Spell.

1712
01:49:46,550 --> 01:49:48,880
Hi.
I'm Tad Lancaster.

1713
01:49:48,880 --> 01:49:52,220
Mr. Marshall thought you might need a place
to sleep tonight.

1714
01:49:52,220 --> 01:49:53,950
Oh, Mr. Marshall.

1715
01:50:05,730 --> 01:50:07,130
Hello?
Hello.

1716
01:50:08,430 --> 01:50:10,540
Sam.

1717
01:50:10,540 --> 01:50:13,070
Sam, I can barely hear you.

1718
01:50:13,070 --> 01:50:16,940
- Is there a verdict yet?
- Yeah. Yeah, it's me.

1719
01:50:16,940 --> 01:50:18,880
Sam, are you there?
Yeah.

1720
01:50:18,880 --> 01:50:21,550
Yes, can you hear me?
Sam?

1721
01:50:21,550 --> 01:50:24,180
Not guilty! We did it!

1722
01:50:25,280 --> 01:50:26,920
- What?
- Not guilty!

1723
01:50:26,920 --> 01:50:28,850
Not guilty!

1724
01:50:28,860 --> 01:50:30,620
Not guilty.

1725
01:50:30,620 --> 01:50:33,190
Not guilty!
Sam!

1726
01:50:33,190 --> 01:50:34,730
Yes!
Oh!

1727
01:50:34,730 --> 01:50:36,160
Yes. We won!

1728
01:50:37,630 --> 01:50:39,530
Sam, I told you.
I told you.

1729
01:50:39,530 --> 01:50:41,600
I told you you could bring it home.
I told you.

1730
01:50:41,600 --> 01:50:43,570
Yeah! Yes, we did it!

1731
01:50:46,570 --> 01:50:49,040
Ah.

1732
01:50:49,040 --> 01:50:51,140
Thurgood,
I'm having trouble hearing you.

1733
01:50:51,140 --> 01:50:53,480
Sam, are you there?
Are you there?

1734
01:50:53,480 --> 01:50:57,480
Thurgood!

1735
01:51:55,310 --> 01:51:57,940
Oh, Luis.
Marshall!

1736
01:51:57,940 --> 01:51:59,980
Your wife still putting up with you?
Look at me.

1737
01:51:59,980 --> 01:52:01,950
She dress me from head to toe.

1738
01:52:01,950 --> 01:52:04,780
Got me looking as sharp as you.

1739
01:52:04,790 --> 01:52:07,020
God bless you.
We really need your help.

1740
01:52:07,020 --> 01:52:10,060
I promise you I'll do everything
in my power to help him.

1741
01:52:10,060 --> 01:52:11,790
Thank you for coming,
Mr. Marshall.

1742
01:52:11,790 --> 01:52:13,690
We really need you in Mississippi.
